735
01:10:20,375 --> 01:10:22,124
- No!
- Where are you going?

736
01:10:22,125 --> 01:10:24,999
Tell this guy enough with the
handyman shit for the day!

737
01:10:25,000 --> 01:10:27,415
- Why?
- Because it's driving me
fucking crazy!

738
01:10:27,416 --> 01:10:30,957
Hello! Stop, fuck off.
There are people in here.

739
01:10:30,958 --> 01:10:33,625
Stop it, asshole! Fuck you!

740
01:10:35,708 --> 01:10:36,958
Are you okay?

741
01:10:40,208 --> 01:10:41,957
I am now.

742
01:10:41,958 --> 01:10:44,457
Is there anything I can do?

743
01:10:44,458 --> 01:10:47,708
Yeah, you can have sex
with me, so I know that I can.

744
01:10:51,208 --> 01:10:53,541
I don't think
that's a good idea.

745
01:11:15,791 --> 01:11:18,999
Hey. All right,
where did you get those?

746
01:11:19,000 --> 01:11:22,415
- Online.
- That simple, huh?

747
01:11:22,416 --> 01:11:25,040
That simple.

748
01:11:25,041 --> 01:11:26,665
Can I try one?

749
01:11:26,666 --> 01:11:29,624
Sure. They're from a shitty
website, so...

750
01:11:29,625 --> 01:11:32,874
they're probably sugar pills,
and they don't do anything,
but yeah.

751
01:11:32,875 --> 01:11:35,707
- Can I try two, then?
- Sure.

752
01:11:35,708 --> 01:11:36,999
Yeah.

753
01:11:37,000 --> 01:11:39,332
Thank you.

754
01:11:39,333 --> 01:11:42,250
- You should swallow the pills.
- That's just how I do it.

755
01:11:44,875 --> 01:11:46,083
Yeah.

756
01:11:47,625 --> 01:11:49,041
I miss you too.

757
01:11:51,375 --> 01:11:53,333
Can I talk to Mommy?

758
01:14:04,958 --> 01:14:07,790
Well, you left in a hurry.

759
01:14:07,791 --> 01:14:10,332
I did.

760
01:14:10,333 --> 01:14:12,500
Joy was pissed.

761
01:14:16,208 --> 01:14:20,250
I, uh... found a name.

762
01:14:22,250 --> 01:14:24,332
Look, I don't know what you're
planning on doing with it,

763
01:14:24,333 --> 01:14:25,665
and...

764
01:14:25,666 --> 01:14:27,791
to be honest,
I don't want to know.

765
01:14:29,875 --> 01:14:34,625
But if you think it's gonna
help in some way, so be it.

766
01:14:37,125 --> 01:14:38,832
Just, uh...

767
01:14:38,833 --> 01:14:41,666
Don't get hurt. Alright?

768
01:16:11,833 --> 01:16:14,874
Once ground zero...

769
01:16:19,333 --> 01:16:23,457
Just a reminder: that guy's
banned from pretty much
every platform.

770
01:16:23,458 --> 01:16:25,624
Enjoy looking at him.

771
01:16:25,625 --> 01:16:26,791
Okay.

772
01:16:28,208 --> 01:16:31,082
And, by the way,
clean your neck, please.

773
01:16:31,083 --> 01:16:32,916
Okay.

774
01:16:34,625 --> 01:16:36,790
Not sure what that has to do
with anything.

775
01:16:36,791 --> 01:16:39,916
She's starting
to fucking lose it.

776
01:16:58,708 --> 01:17:00,083
Holy shit.

777
01:17:02,375 --> 01:17:06,332
You know what?
I don't think anyone is
going to recognize you.

778
01:17:06,333 --> 01:17:08,082
You did.

779
01:17:08,083 --> 01:17:11,207
Yeah, 'cause I was there, I
remember what you were wearing.

780
01:17:11,208 --> 01:17:13,500
I can barely see your face
in the video.

781
01:17:28,125 --> 01:17:31,791
So was it like kind of
self-defense or kind of?

782
01:17:33,791 --> 01:17:34,916
No.

783
01:17:39,875 --> 01:17:41,291
No?

784
01:17:43,458 --> 01:17:44,666
No.

785
01:17:47,041 --> 01:17:49,332
Okay. What do you want me to do?

786
01:17:49,333 --> 01:17:51,457
I don't know.
It's your ticket, not mine.

787
01:17:51,458 --> 01:17:53,874
It doesn't break
any of our rules,

788
01:17:53,875 --> 01:17:55,915
so deleting it might bring
more attention.

789
01:17:55,916 --> 01:17:57,541
I don't want to get you
into any trouble.

790
01:18:01,125 --> 01:18:03,082
Maybe I deserve
to be in trouble.

791
01:18:03,083 --> 01:18:04,624
Daisy, it's not you.

792
01:18:04,625 --> 01:18:07,500
It's this fucking place,
it's not you.

793
01:18:09,166 --> 01:18:12,207
It's got a lot of views. The
guy never filed a police report.

794
01:18:12,208 --> 01:18:16,458
I checked, so you're probably
in the clear.

795
01:18:20,125 --> 01:18:23,375
Still, though,
it's so fucking ugly.

796
01:18:24,791 --> 01:18:28,125
"Girls boss destroys."

797
01:18:29,833 --> 01:18:31,791
Yeah, it's ugly.

798
01:19:19,208 --> 01:19:22,250
I went on a date...
or I tried to.

799
01:19:24,541 --> 01:19:27,500
But I got upset, and I left.

800
01:19:34,125 --> 01:19:38,040
We're-we're supposed to talk
about work-related issues.

801
01:19:38,041 --> 01:19:40,832
Yes, I left because of a ticket.

802
01:19:40,833 --> 01:19:44,082
Okay, and what specifically
about this ticket

803
01:19:44,083 --> 01:19:46,707
made you do that?

804
01:19:46,708 --> 01:19:49,540
It bothered me.

805
01:19:49,541 --> 01:19:51,999
Can you explain why?

806
01:19:52,000 --> 01:19:55,207
Sometimes vocalizing an image

807
01:19:55,208 --> 01:19:57,666
stuck in your head
can help root it out.

808
01:20:00,500 --> 01:20:03,124
Well, you make that sound easy.

809
01:20:03,125 --> 01:20:04,875
Just give it a go.

810
01:20:07,916 --> 01:20:09,458
Um...

811
01:20:13,708 --> 01:20:17,833
Mmm. People want to hurt people.

812
01:20:20,708 --> 01:20:26,624
Okay, so in this video there
was an act of violence.

813
01:20:26,625 --> 01:20:30,541
Yes, and it made me want to
hurt someone too.

814
01:20:34,333 --> 01:20:36,415
I see.

815
01:20:36,416 --> 01:20:41,707
You know, sometimes
when I go for a run, um,

816
01:20:41,708 --> 01:20:46,082
to pump myself up, I daydream
about getting into a fight,

817
01:20:46,083 --> 01:20:49,665
defending my wife, punching
some jerk for accosting her.

818
01:20:49,666 --> 01:20:52,499
It's quite a common fantasy,
but it's not a healthy one.

819
01:20:52,500 --> 01:20:56,915
It's actually quite selfish
putting someone else
in a position of danger

820
01:20:56,916 --> 01:20:59,207
to make myself feel empowered.

821
01:20:59,208 --> 01:21:02,290
But if that actually happened,
you wouldn't be putting her
in danger.

822
01:21:02,291 --> 01:21:03,999
You'd be protecting her from it.

823
01:21:04,000 --> 01:21:07,540
Sure, but my point is,
in these situations,

824
01:21:07,541 --> 01:21:12,290
we tend to ignore the victim
and focus instead
on the villain.

825
01:21:12,291 --> 01:21:15,999
We funnel our energy
into revenge or justice

826
01:21:16,000 --> 01:21:21,041
or whatever you want to call it,
and we develop a hero complex.

827
01:21:23,750 --> 01:21:28,165
But you're not the hero here,
Daisy. This isn't some
detective story.

828
01:21:28,166 --> 01:21:30,874
You're just a regular person
doing a regular job.

829
01:21:30,875 --> 01:21:33,082
Yes, thank you.

830
01:21:33,083 --> 01:21:37,290
But maybe the girl
in the video wants that guy
to suffer like she did.

831
01:21:37,291 --> 01:21:40,083
It's what I would want.

832
01:21:43,291 --> 01:21:45,457
You have an impulse, yeah?

833
01:21:45,458 --> 01:21:47,957
To take action,
which is a wonderful thing.

834
01:21:47,958 --> 01:21:50,624
Unless that impulse is to do
something not wonderful.

835
01:21:50,625 --> 01:21:53,875
- It is not an impulse.
- What is it then?

836
01:21:55,333 --> 01:21:57,915
I try to forget, and I keep
getting reminded

837
01:21:57,916 --> 01:22:00,499
over and over,
and I know it sounds crazy,

838
01:22:00,500 --> 01:22:02,749
but it feels like the universe
is telling me:

839
01:22:02,750 --> 01:22:05,249
"Go find this guy!"

840
01:22:05,250 --> 01:22:08,207
because it feels like our
fates are intertwined,

841
01:22:08,208 --> 01:22:12,583
and I can't feel free until I
fucking do something about it.

842
01:22:13,666 --> 01:22:15,915
But that's simply not true,
Daisy.

843
01:22:15,916 --> 01:22:17,790
How do you know that?

844
01:22:17,791 --> 01:22:23,000
Because if it were true, you'd
be talking to him now, not me.

845
01:22:31,458 --> 01:22:33,832
Just a sec, wait. What?

846
01:22:33,833 --> 01:22:36,249
I quit.

847
01:22:36,250 --> 01:22:38,874
Your employee contract
requires two weeks' notice

848
01:22:38,875 --> 01:22:40,874
before resignation takes effect.

849
01:22:40,875 --> 01:22:43,165
If you don't oblige,
we'll take it to court.

850
01:22:43,166 --> 01:22:44,958
Two weeks it is.

851
01:23:26,875 --> 01:23:28,249
No!

852
01:23:28,250 --> 01:23:30,457
Fuck! No!

853
01:23:30,458 --> 01:23:31,999
Fuck! Aah!

854
01:23:32,000 --> 01:23:33,791
Poor guy.

855
01:23:34,875 --> 01:23:35,916
Fuck!

856
01:25:41,250 --> 01:25:43,208
Don't fucking do it, bro.

857
01:26:13,500 --> 01:26:14,708
Okay, I get it.

858
01:26:47,083 --> 01:26:48,666
Daisy Morris?

859
01:26:54,875 --> 01:26:57,582
Tell me something
you learned at your last job.

860
01:26:57,583 --> 01:27:02,415
Well, I was in tech,
and while I learned
nothing about computers,

861
01:27:02,416 --> 01:27:04,415
it taught me a lot about people.

862
01:27:04,416 --> 01:27:08,290
Because that's what the
internet is. It's just people.

863
01:27:08,291 --> 01:27:11,624
And for a while my biggest
desire was to help these people,

864
01:27:11,625 --> 01:27:14,040
which is why I wanted
to be a nurse.

865
01:27:14,041 --> 01:27:17,457
Yes, that's why many
young men and women
enter the field of medicine.

866
01:27:17,458 --> 01:27:19,665
I'm sure you hear this
all the time, but...

867
01:27:19,666 --> 01:27:25,624
we think we need to devote
ourselves to something
noble and altruistic.

868
01:27:25,625 --> 01:27:30,165
Something that makes our lives
meaningful and important,

869
01:27:30,166 --> 01:27:34,374
but this job taught me that
not everyone deserves...

870
01:27:34,375 --> 01:27:35,957
help.

871
01:27:35,958 --> 01:27:40,165
Some people deserve
the opposite.

872
01:27:40,166 --> 01:27:42,749
I realize that's not the best
thing to say in a job interview,

873
01:27:42,750 --> 01:27:44,540
but what I'm getting at is:

874
01:27:44,541 --> 01:27:48,374
I have learned how to hold
myself and others to task.

875
01:27:48,375 --> 01:27:50,290
That's a good skill. Very good.

876
01:27:50,291 --> 01:27:52,165
Another thing I learned:

877
01:27:52,166 --> 01:27:53,790
There are three types of people:

878
01:27:53,791 --> 01:27:56,457
people who make the world
better,

879
01:27:56,458 --> 01:27:58,332
people who make the world worse,

880
01:27:58,333 --> 01:28:00,832
and people who watch.

881
01:28:00,833 --> 01:28:03,833
Most people, they watch.

882
01:28:05,166 --> 01:28:07,125
That's it. That's all they do.

883
01:28:08,916 --> 01:28:11,083
I would rather be
one of the other two.

884
01:28:12,625 --> 01:28:14,250
Let me make sure
I have this correct:

885
01:28:15,208 --> 01:28:18,582
You'd rather make the world
worse than do nothing?

886
01:28:18,583 --> 01:28:20,124
Yes.

887
01:28:20,125 --> 01:28:22,290
Okay, now you lost me.

888
01:28:22,291 --> 01:28:25,374
Well, bad things happen
no matter what.

889
01:28:25,375 --> 01:28:28,124
And sometimes the only way to
stop a bad thing...

890
01:28:28,125 --> 01:28:30,999
...is with another bad thing.

891
01:28:31,000 --> 01:28:33,957
You know, I'm not sure I agree
with you there.

892
01:28:33,958 --> 01:28:35,999
Well, I figured you wouldn't.

893
01:28:36,000 --> 01:28:38,333
- Is that right?
- Yeah.

894
01:28:40,458 --> 01:28:42,707
As interesting
as all this may be,

895
01:28:42,708 --> 01:28:46,124
